README for 460 Project (Catherine Lai & Andrew Clausen)
-------------------------------------------------------

SETTING UP
----------
Before starting, we recommend adding some directories and symlinks:

	mkdir save
	ln [nltk-data-dir] data


TESTING/USING
-------------
See the instructions at the end of the report.

Here are the example commands from the report:

	./train save/classifier sci.med soc.religion.christian comp.graphics
	./classify save/classifier data/sci.space/59848
	./train --corpus-size 700 save/classifier sci.med soc.religion.christian
	./accuracy save/classifier sci.med soc.religion.christian

Here are the help screens for train, classify and accuracy:

        use: train [<options>] <output-classifier> { <group> }+
        options:
        -c n, --context n      maximum context size (default 3)
        -t n, --top n          top n words allowed context (default 500)
        -n n, --corpus-size n  maxmimum number of items to use from corpus
        -m, --male-female      build a male/female classifier
        -r, --rel-entropy      use relative entropy for classification
        -i, --min-info         use min. information for classification

        use: classify <classifier> { <email> }+

        use: accuracy [<options>] <classifier> { <group> }+
        options:
        -a, --avoid-training   don't test on training data
        -n n, --corpus-size n  maxmimum number of items to use from corpus
        -t, --test-training    test on training data


NOTES
-----
[1] Classifier files are of the order of 10 Mb.  It can take a minute to
read/write them over NFS!

[2] It usually takes about 10 minutes to train a classifier on the CS machines.
The progress meter is usually accurate.

